						<summary>

						<p>This undated inscription records that a certain brave warrior who was the son of <hi rend="bold">Vīrasatti,</hi> a servant of the <hi rend="bold">Baidumba</hi> king, fought in the battle of <hi rend="bold">Tiruvaḷa</hi> and died. A number of epithets describing his bravery are found in the record. </p>						

						</summary>
